      "uuid": "f9353542-a65d-44a8-9b01-2dff1f9d748b",
      "text": " The image shows a cartoon from Peanuts where a character is sitting at a yellow booth with a sign that reads \"PSYCHIATRIC HELP 5\u00a2\" and \"THE DOCTOR IS IN\" with an \"IN\" card. The text on the booth appears to be hand-drawn in a casual, somewhat childlike print style.\n\nThis isn't a specific font in the traditional sense, but rather the distinctive hand lettering style of Charles Schulz, the creator of Peanuts. If you're looking for fonts that mimic this style, you might consider:\n\n1. Comic Sans MS (though this is more polished than Schulz's style)\n2. Schulz's Fonts or Peanuts Font (fonts specifically designed to mimic his handwriting)\n3. Casual handwritten fonts like \"Chalkboard\" or \"School Book\"\n\nThe text has an informal, somewhat wobbly quality with uneven letter sizes and spacing, characteristic of hand-drawn lettering rather than typeset text. If you need something similar for a project, look for fonts described as \"comic book style,\" \"cartoon handwriting,\" or \"casual handwritten.\"",
      "sender": "assistant",
      "index": 1,
      "created_at": "2025-03-06T02:33:15.627448Z",
      "updated_at": "2025-03-06T02:33:15.627448Z",
